HEADWORD: Thiosulphuric
<hw>Thi`o*sul*phur"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thio-</ets> + <ets>sulphuric</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, an unstable acid,
<chform>H2S2O3</chform>, analogous to sulphuric acid, and formerly
called <altname>hyposulphurous acid</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

